<subSubSection box="[132,277,534,560]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[130,777,534,911]" box="[132,277,534,560]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582">COMPARISON</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[130,777,534,911]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582">
The new genus is characterized by large acanthostyles with narrow sheaths, cystose mesozooecia and presence of cystiphragms. It shows some similarities to the Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorjunova, 2005" authorityName="Gorjunova" authorityYear="2005" class="Stenolaemata" family="Ralfimartitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trepostomatida" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="family">
Ralfimartitidae 
<bibRefCitation author="GORJUNOVA R. V." box="[130,324,661,688]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" pagination="51 - 63" refId="ref20505" refString="GORJUNOVA R. V. 2005. - Ralfimartitidae, a new family of Paleozoic bryozoans of the order Trepostomida. Paleontologicheskii Zhurnal 2: 51 - 63 [in Russian]." type="journal article" year="2005">Gorjunova, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="GORJUNOVA R. V." box="[341,541,661,688]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" pagination="51 - 63" refId="ref20505" refString="GORJUNOVA R. V. 2005. - Ralfimartitidae, a new family of Paleozoic bryozoans of the order Trepostomida. Paleontologicheskii Zhurnal 2: 51 - 63 [in Russian]." type="journal article" year="2005">Gorjunova (2005)</bibRefCitation>
introduced the term “aulozooecia” for structures characteristic for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorjunova" authorityYear="2005" box="[608,773,693,719]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Ralfimartitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trepostomatida" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="family">Ralfimartitidae</taxonomicName>
. The “aulozooecia” represent indeed large acanthostyles filled out by a hyaline skeletal material (see also Tavener-Smith 1969). The most similar genus in the Family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorjunova" authorityYear="2005" box="[595,754,789,815]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Ralfimartitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trepostomatida" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="family">Ralfimartitidae</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorjunova, 2005" authorityName="Gorjunova" authorityYear="2005" box="[130,434,821,848]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Ralfimartitidae" genus="Rozhnovites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trepostomatida" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[130,248,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="582">Rozhnovites</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="GORJUNOVA R. V." box="[255,434,821,848]" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" pagination="51 - 63" refId="ref20505" refString="GORJUNOVA R. V. 2005. - Ralfimartitidae, a new family of Paleozoic bryozoans of the order Trepostomida. Paleontologicheskii Zhurnal 2: 51 - 63 [in Russian]." type="journal article" year="2005">Gorjunova, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ernst &amp; Carrera" authorityYear="2022" box="[631,773,821,847]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Trematoporidae" genus="Argentinopora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trepostomatida" pageId="21" pageNumber="582" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[631,773,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="582">Argentinopora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in annulated arrangement of autozooecia and mesozooecia, as well as in absence of cystiphragms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
